children.subject: My understanding that they're no reserved seats over the summer. That has been the case for years, and I don't think it will change. Summer courses results in a net profit, so usually they accept everyone who can pay.

history.content: Follow-up should be correct (there are no restrictions) @16779_f15

In light of the new enrollment changes, where non-CS majors/minors will not be able to take upper division CS courses in coming Fall and Spring Semester, will Upper division CS courses still be open for enrollment to all during the summer as they have been previously, or will new restrictions apply? I ask because I am not a CS major and plan on taking CS upper divs next summer, will this be possible? thank you,
